Date: 6/1/1911
Source: Ohinemuri Gazette
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: "He called me a 'shelfer,'" said a witness at the Magistrate's Court, Christchurch. "A what?" enquired Mr T. A. B. Bailey, S.M., who was on the Bench. Mr Hunter (who appeared for the complainant): "The word is not in the Oxford dictionary, your Worship; it is a slang term for a man who gives information to the police."
