Date: 0/0/1949
Source: Dictionary of the Underworld
Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page: 616
Edition:
Quote: One who, upon a companion or an associate, informs to the police: New Zealand since ca. 1925; and by 1935 at latest, Australian: 1932 Nelson Baylis (private letter) 1941, Sidney J. Baker, New Zealand Slang; 1942, Baker, Australian Slang; extant. He `shelfs' the victim: cf. shelf, on the, sense 2. and shelf, 3, which may consti- tute the imm. origin ... The same as shelfer: Australian: since ca. 1920. Jice Doon, 1926, Baker, 1942, Baker, in these Australian c. synonyms or `informer': crab, copper-nark, dead-copper, dropper- man, fizgig, fiz, shelf, shelfer, stinker, top-off.
